snippet.textDisplay:
Jimmy Johnson’s reaction was like:
1) A little kid who just got the very best gift he could ever ask for (the fight to talk while happily crying).
2) A father who just received the best gift or news he’s ever received, as his son (Troy) is moved to tears in adoration of his dad, and in awe and pride in seeing his dad in a moment of pure happiness and appreciation of something that brought such joy to dad.

Very well done, coach. You earned it. I can’t think of any other coach who was or is as passionate about the game as you. Congratulations!

I’m still in tears while typing this. I’ll be watching this video repeatedly...

snippet.textDisplay:
I am sooo happy for him!
This diehard Rival fan in AFC EAST was a teenager and arrogant af in the Dallas/Bills superbowl.
And lived in Miami When JJ was a Dolphins coach..
~We all know his awesome Dallas story BUT his
Dolphins story was epic..From the last 2 years of him lurking on his fishing boat in the FL Keys & constantly being rumored for the Dolphins job,,
Was a disgusting end to The Don Shula Legacy but this is about JJ...
~He drafted such amazing & I mean Superstar players in Miami.
Pat Surtain ,Sam Madison,,Zach Thomas,,Jason Taylor,Konrad..
That defense was amazing.
It is hands down my ALLTIME most hated defense since I've been a fan.
Madison,Surtain,Zach,TimBowens,JasonTaylor,,Brock Marion,,Trace Armstrong..
This was an era where I hated with a passion my rival teams but respected them with almost equal passion..
